Video Title: Top 10 Teenagers Who Had Insane Plastic Surgery
Comment Content: In my honest opinion, the bullying that takes place toward people who are "different" needs to be addressed as a society rather than expecting people to change in drastic ways in order to "fit-the-norm." Everyone has something about themselves that they don't like, but if it is something that is not harmful other than "you just don't like it," why the extreme measures to be rid of it? I think plastic surgery can be beneficial in many situations (i.e.: someone's body was disfigured in a car accident and needs it for reconstruction or the way that someone's nose naturally is is out of alignment and causing difficulty breathing at times). I find it sad that people who are so young are feeling pressured to do this, or are just doing this because they want to; without the development and maturity to consider their futures and how this may negatively effect them. Ultimately, everyone has the right to choose what they do with their own bodies, but I hope that (aside from extreme circumstances - as previously mentioned) limitations are placed so that children are not doing this to themselves without thinking things through, but instead are needing to wait until they are adults (18 years of age here, as it is with the laws concerning cigarettes). That being said, sadly that does not mean that they would not find a way of accomplishing this by illegal means (again, as it is with cigarettes) which could be even more dangerous.
